narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Theories of history; historiography in modern European intellectual and cultural history
A thorough overview of the recent historiography and philosophy of cultural/intellectual history. A great readings course for those interested in German and French history, in particular.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The course only was perfect. The class was intimate and engaged every session, and the reading list is phenomenal. The paper was fun, and the classes where we discussed papers were super helpful.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, will help you think clearly about historical method and important question in European intellectual and cultural history.

I would recommend this course to any students of students interested in addressing the historical and philosophical questions of interest in the 21st century. Any students of history, philosophy, or the humanities could stand to benefit from taking this course.
